# ==============================================================================
# .gitignore — Academic Claude Code Projects
# ==============================================================================

# --- LaTeX build artifacts ---
# Bare *.log and *.out are NOT used — they collide with Stata logs and
# shell nohup.out, respectively. Scope both to LaTeX directories.
*.aux
*.bbl
*.bcf
*.blg
*.fdb_latexmk
*.fls
*.lof
*.lot
*.nav
*.run.xml
*.snm
*.synctex.gz
*.toc
*.vrb
*-blx.bib
paper/**/*.log
paper/**/*.out
talks/**/*.log
talks/**/*.out
slides/**/*.log
slides/**/*.out
supplementary/**/*.log
supplementary/**/*.out

# --- Stata terminal background-run artifacts ---
# `stata -b do do/main.do` writes a batch auto-log named after the do-file
# (e.g. main.log) into the working directory (repo root); a `nohup ... &`
# launch writes nohup.out. Both capture the entire run and can exceed GitHub's
# 100 MB file limit (this is what blocked the server push 2026-06-08).
# Anchored leading-slash + the log/ subdir mean these match ONLY root-level
# files — the curated per-file logs under log/<reldir>/ stay tracked.
/*.log
nohup.out

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.venv/
venv/
env/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Always track dependency manifests (anti-rules — never ignore these)
!requirements.txt
!requirements-*.txt
!environment.yml
!pyproject.toml
!Pipfile
!Pipfile.lock

# --- R ---
.Rproj.user/
.Rhistory
.RData
.Rdata
.Ruserdata

# --- OS ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Claude Code (local-only, not shared across machines) ---
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/state/*
!.claude/state/primary_source_surnames.txt
!.claude/state/verification-ledger.md
.claude/worktrees/
CLAUDE.local.md

# --- IDE / editor noise ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# --- Quarto ---
/.quarto/

# --- Compiled PDFs (uncomment per project to track specific outputs) ---
# *.pdf

# --- Output artifacts (uncomment per project) ---
# *.rds
# output/**/*.rds

# --- Academic PDFs ---
# Default: gitignored to keep the template repo small (PDFs don't diff well
# and bloat git history). In a fork where paper PDFs are load-bearing,
# enable Git LFS and comment these lines out — see
# .claude/rules/data-version-control.md (when present) or
# quality_reports/plans/*lfs-dvc-migration-plan.md.
master_supporting_docs/literature/papers/*.pdf
master_supporting_docs/literature/papers/**/*.pdf

# ==============================================================================
# RESTRICTED DATA + ESTIMATES (air-gap; never push from Scribe to remote)
# ==============================================================================
# data/      = raw row-level CalSCHLS / CDE student records (restricted PII)
# estimates/ = .ster + va_<outcome>_all.dta (large derived from restricted data)
# Per .claude/rules/air-gapped-workflow.md, only .gitkeep stubs are tracked
# to preserve directory structure on clone.  Pre-push enforcement lives in
# `.githooks/pre-push` — install on each machine with:
#     git config core.hooksPath .githooks

/data/*
!/data/.gitkeep
!/data/raw/
!/data/cleaned/
/data/raw/*
!/data/raw/.gitkeep
!/data/raw/upstream/
/data/raw/upstream/*
!/data/raw/upstream/.gitkeep
!/data/raw/upstream/README.md
/data/cleaned/*
!/data/cleaned/.gitkeep

/estimates/*
!/estimates/.gitkeep
